The Letšeng mine in Lesotho has produced a 101 ct diamond, bringing the total recoveries to a record 14 diamonds of more than 100 ct during the year, London-listed Gem Diamonds reported on Wednesday. Besides the 101 ct diamond, the miner also extracted a 71 ct white Type IIa diamond. Letšeng is the highest dollar per carat kimberlite mine in the world.